comments: Harris (ORL) does not step out of bounds as he attempts to save the ball.
Banchero (ORL) is moving alongside Butler's (MIA) path and marginal contact occurs as Butler cuts back towards the rim.
Harris (ORL) brings his hands slightly forward towards Butler (MIA) and marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Harris (ORL) does not step out of bounds when he receives the ball on the perimeter.
Butler (MIA) legally contests Banchero's (ORL) jump shot attempt.
Banchero (ORL) is the last player to touch the ball before the ball goes out of bounds.  Possession is correctly awarded to Miami.
Adebayo (MIA) establishes himself in Fultz's (ORL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Adebayo (MIA) fails to fully clear the lane and is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Lowry (MIA) cleanly deflects the ball away from Fultz (ORL).
Suggs (ORL) makes contact with the ball and with the part of Lowry's (MIA) hand that is on the ball as he defends the driving shot attempt.
Fultz (ORL) cleanly blocks Lowry's (MIA) shot attempt while the ball is still on its upward flight to the rim, and before the ball touches the backboard.
Fultz (ORL) is bracing for the contact from Strus (MIA) and marginal contact occurs as Fultz releases away from the contact.
Carter Jr. (ORL) jumps alongside Adebayo's (MIA) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Strus (MIA) brings his hand towards Suggs' (ORL) upper body and marginal contact occurs as Suggs mistimes his jump for the rebound.
Adebayo (MIA) deflects the ball away from Fultz (ORL), and the ensuing contact is incidental.

Replay review of the foul called on Banchero (ORL) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful.  Banchero legally contests Butler's (MIA) jump shot and incidental contact occurs after Butler has returned to the floor.  Miami had imminent possession at the time of the whistle, and play resumes with Miami ball.
Lowry (MIA) is already in Banchero's (ORL) path and absorbs the contact.
Butler (MIA) and Fultz (ORL) briefly engage and disengage as marginal contact occurs off ball.
Vincent (MIA) commits a take foul on Suggs (ORL).
Vincent (MIA) brings his forearm towards Suggs' (ORL) path and marginal contact occurs as Suggs moves towards the perimeter.
Vincent (MIA) commits a take foul on Suggs (ORL).
Lowry (MIA) inbounds the ball within five seconds.
Strus (MIA) establishes himself in Suggs's (ORL) path and marginal contact occurs as the screen is set.
Carter Jr. (ORL) legally contests Butler's (MIA) jump shot attempt.
